The paper involves developing a memory-augmented neural agent that hierarchically models multiple levels of decision-making and an imitation learning algorithm that teaches the agent to avoid repeating past mistakes while predicting its own chances of making future progress. These techniques are commonly used in the fields of artificial intelligence (cs.AI), natural language processing (cs.CL), computer vision (cs.CV), and machine learning (cs.LG). Additionally, the paper involves navigation tasks, which are often studied in the field of robotics (cs.RO).
